<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-471-467  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 471 467.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Sept 24 1990 n609 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Study: export control hurts.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Government restrictions on the export of technology are hurting UScompetitiveness in the world market, according to a report fromthe Economic Policy Institute.andP;  About 40 percent of US industrialexports require a license to leave the docks.andP;  Most of therestrictions are mandated by the Pentagon for national securityreasons.andP;  The report says that those restrictions have gone farbeyond their original purpose.andP;  Congress is in the middle ofdeciding whether to extend the Export Administration Act foranother five years.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ExportWorld MarketGovernment RegulationForeign CompetitionEconomic Policy Institute.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>